A Prime Number is a number greater than 1 that has no divisors other than 1 and itself.

For example:

7 → Divisors: 1, 7 → Prime

10 → Divisors: 1, 2, 5, 10 → Not Prime

Write a program to check whether a given number is a prime number or not.

Input Format

A single positive integer N.

Constraints

1 ≤ N ≤ 10⁶

Output Format

Print "Prime Number" if the number is prime, otherwise print "Not a Prime Number".

Sample Input 0

7
Sample Output 0

Prime Number
Sample Input 1

10
Sample Output 1

Not a Prime Number

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <stdbool.h>

bool isPrime(int n){
    if (n == 1 || n == 0)
        return false;
    for (int i = 2; i <n; i++) {
        if (n % i == 0)
            return false;
    }
    return true;
}


int main()
{
    int N ;
    scanf("%d",&N);
        
        if (isPrime(N))
            printf("Prime Number");
        else
            printf("Not a Prime Number");

    return 0;
}


